Definition: possessing or displaying courage
Example: able to face and deal with danger or fear without flinching; Familiarity with danger makes a brave man braver but less daring- Herman Melville; a frank courageous heart...triumphed over pain- William Wordsworth; set a courageous example by leading them safely into and out of enemy-held territory
Synonyms: noun, attribute, braveness, COWARDLY, courageous, courage, courageousness, ADVENTUROUS, BOLD, RESOLUTE, UNAFRAID, possessing, or, displaying, able, to, face, and, deal, with, danger, fear, without, flinching, Familiarity, makes, a, brave, man, braver, but, less, daring, -, Herman, Melville, frank, heart, triumphed, over, pain, William, Wordsworth, set, example, by, leading, them, safely, into, out, of, enemy-held, territory
Category: adj.all
